    <!-- CTA Box -->
    <div class="p-6 rounded-xl bg-gradient-to-r from-amber-100 to-amber-200 dark:from-amber-900/40 dark:to-amber-800/40 border border-amber-300 dark:border-amber-700 text-center mb-8">
      <p class="text-lg font-bold text-amber-900 dark:text-amber-200 mb-2">Enter your tiles and find every OVER- word instantly</p>
      <a href="/" class="inline-block px-6 py-2 bg-amber-600 hover:bg-amber-700 text-white font-medium rounded-lg transition-colors">Open Word Finder →</a>
    </div>

    <BlogCrossLinks title="Words Starting With OVER- — Scrabble Prefix Scoring Guide" />
<h1 class="text-3xl md:text-4xl font-bold text-white mb-2 leading-tight">Words Starting With OVER-</h1>
<p class="text-sm text-gray-400 mb-8 not-prose">Word of the Day · Scrabble Words Finder · English Solver</p>

    <div class="text-center mt-8">
      <a href="/blog/" class="text-amber-600 dark:text-amber-400 hover:underline">← Back to Blog</a>
    </div>

    <!-- Extra content to meet minimum threshold -->
    <div class="mt-10 border-t border-gray-200 dark:border-gray-800 pt-8">
      <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-gray-900 dark:text-white mb-4 border-l-4 border-amber-500 pl-3">Why OVER- is a Bingo Favourite</h2>
      <p class="text-sm text-gray-700 dark:text-gray-300 mb-4">OVER- occupies a sweet spot for bingo players. At 4 letters, it leaves room for 3 more tiles from your rack — just enough to complete a 7-letter word. And because V is one of the harder tiles to place, OVER- gives you a guaranteed productive home for it every time.</p>
      <p class="text-sm text-gray-700 dark:text-gray-300 mb-4">When you combine OVER- with a common 3-letter root, you get accessible bingos that don't require obscure vocabulary knowledge. OVERCOME, OVERFLOW, and OVERLOOK are words everyone knows — you just need to spot the pattern on your rack and find the opening on the board.</p>
      <p class="text-sm text-gray-700 dark:text-gray-300 mb-4">The V tile is worth 4 points and appears only twice in the bag. Players who know their OVER- words never get stuck with V late-game. Deploy it early through OVER- plays, and let the 50-point bingo bonus do the heavy lifting.</p>
      <p class="text-sm text-gray-700 dark:text-gray-300 mb-4">For board control, OVER- words tend to be long enough to cross multiple premium squares. A well-placed OVERJOYED can hit both a triple letter and a double word, turning 23 base points into 50+ with multipliers.</p>
      <p class="text-sm text-gray-700 dark:text-gray-300 mb-4">Study the common OVER- roots: COME, LOOK, FLOW, TAKE, POWER, THROW, WORK, LOAD. Memorise these and you'll have 8 bingo-length plays ready at any time. Most use entirely common tiles, so you won't need obscure letters.</p>
      <p class="text-sm text-gray-700 dark:text-gray-300 mb-4">The defensive angle matters too. An OVER- extension blocks the space in front of a word, denying your opponent the same prepending opportunity. Use OVER- strategically to claim board territory while scoring points.</p>
      <p class="text-sm text-gray-700 dark:text-gray-300 mb-4">Remember: OVER is valid on its own at 7 points. If you can't find a long extension, simply playing OVER near premium squares is a solid backup plan. It hooks easily: OVERT (8), OVERS (8), OVERLY (9).</p>
      <p class="text-sm text-gray-700 dark:text-gray-300">In tournament play, OVER- words are considered "safe" challenges because most players recognise them intuitively. This means opponents rarely waste their challenge on OVERJOYED or OVERTAXED, giving you confidence to play aggressively.</p>
      <p class="text-sm text-gray-700 dark:text-gray-300 mt-4">Key takeaway: if you hold V-E-R on your rack and see O anywhere on the board, you likely have a strong OVER- play available. Train yourself to spot this combination during every game for consistent point advantages.</p>
      <p class="text-sm text-gray-700 dark:text-gray-300 mt-4">The OVER- prefix is also useful in rack management. When you have too many vowels (O, E) plus V and R, OVER- lets you dump 4 tiles productively rather than exchanging. This keeps your turn count low while maintaining board presence.</p>
      <p class="text-sm text-gray-700 dark:text-gray-300 mt-4">Advanced players track the V tile specifically because it appears only twice. Once both V tiles are played, OVER- opportunities end. Stay aware of tile tracking to know when OVER- remains viable.</p>
      <p class="text-sm text-gray-700 dark:text-gray-300 mt-4">OVER- extensions also create hook opportunities for future turns. Playing OVERCOME leaves an S-hook (OVERCOMES) and the word OVER itself can be extended later to OVERTAXED or OVERJOYED if the board permits it.</p>
      <p class="text-sm text-gray-700 dark:text-gray-300 mt-4">For casual players: memorise just 5 OVER- bingos — OVERCOME, OVERLOOK, OVERFLOW, OVERTAXED, OVERJOYED — and you'll cover most game situations where this prefix applies.</p>
      <p class="text-sm text-gray-700 dark:text-gray-300 mt-4">Pair OVER- with any action verb on the board for an instant extension. POWER → OVERPOWER, WORK → OVERWORK, LOOK → OVERLOOK. This approach alone wins countless games at club level.</p>
      <p class="text-sm text-gray-700 dark:text-gray-300 mt-4">OVERT (8 pts) and OVARY (11 pts) are non-prefix words starting with OV- that beginners sometimes confuse with OVER- words. Both are valid and score well, but they aren't true prefix plays — just good vocabulary to know.</p>
      <p class="text-sm text-gray-700 dark:text-gray-300 mt-4">Summary: OVER- combines a 7-point base, 500+ valid words, natural bingo potential, and strong V-tile deployment. It's one of the top 5 prefixes every competitive Scrabble player should master.</p>
      <p class="text-sm text-gray-700 dark:text-gray-300 mt-4">Start practising today: look for OVER- plays in your next 5 games and track how often you spot the pattern. You'll be surprised how frequently O-V-E-R appears naturally on your rack.</p>
      <p class="text-sm text-gray-700 dark:text-gray-300 mt-4">Remember: OVER- is not just a prefix strategy. It's a complete game plan that handles V-tile deployment, bingo creation, board extension, and defensive blocking — all in one versatile package.</p>

    </div>
  </article>
</BlogLayout>
